body:
### Component

Forge

### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?

- [X] Foundry
- [ ] Foundryup

### What version of Foundry are you on?

forge 0.2.0 (70f4fb5 2022-11-03T00:10:56.325545Z)

### What command(s) is the bug in?

forge fmt

### Operating System

_No response_

### Describe the bug

Before:

```solidity
/// @notice A proof-of-concept implementation demonstrating how Flexible Voting can be used to allow holders of
/// governance tokens to use them in DeFi but still participate in governance. The FractionalPool simulates a
/// lending protocol, such as Compound Finance or Aave, in that:
///
/// - Tokens can be deposited into the Pool by suppliers
/// - Tokens can be withdrawn from the Pool by borrowers
/// - Depositors are able to express their vote preferences on individual governance proposals
/// - The vote preferences of all Depositors are expressed proportionally across any tokens held by the pool, and
///   rolled up into a single delegated vote made by the pool before the proposal is completed
contract FractionalPool {}
```

After `forge fmt` with wrap comments enabled and line length of 100:

```solidity
/// @notice A proof-of-concept implementation demonstrating how Flexible Voting can be used to allow
/// holders of
/// governance tokens to use them in DeFi but still participate in governance. The FractionalPool
/// simulates a
/// lending protocol, such as Compound Finance or Aave, in that:
///
/// - Tokens can be deposited into the Pool by suppliers
/// - Tokens can be withdrawn from the Pool by borrowers
/// - Depositors are able to express their vote preferences on individual governance proposals
/// - The vote preferences of all Depositors are expressed proportionally across any tokens held by
/// the pool, and
///   rolled up into a single delegated vote made by the pool before the proposal is completed
```

You can see the line breaks are preserved, but they shouldn't be. The file that's from is here: https://github.com/ScopeLift/flexible-voting/blob/master/src/FractionalPool.sol

If using rustfmt, here is the before:

```rust
// @notice A proof-of-concept implementation demonstrating how Flexible Voting can be used to allow holders of
// governance tokens to use them in DeFi but still participate in governance. The FractionalPool simulates a
// lending protocol, such as Compound Finance or Aave, in that:
//
// - Tokens can be deposited into the Pool by suppliers
// - Tokens can be withdrawn from the Pool by borrowers
// - Depositors are able to express their vote preferences on individual governance proposals
// - The vote preferences of all Depositors are expressed proportionally across any tokens held by the pool, and
//   rolled up into a single delegated vote made by the pool before the proposal is completed
```

And after:

```rust
// @notice A proof-of-concept implementation demonstrating how Flexible Voting can be used to allow
// holders of governance tokens to use them in DeFi but still participate in governance. The
// FractionalPool simulates a lending protocol, such as Compound Finance or Aave, in that:
//
// - Tokens can be deposited into the Pool by suppliers
// - Tokens can be withdrawn from the Pool by borrowers
// - Depositors are able to express their vote preferences on individual governance proposals
// - The vote preferences of all Depositors are expressed proportionally across any tokens held by
//   the pool, and rolled up into a single delegated vote made by the pool before the proposal is
//   completed
```
